Gearing up for the COVID-19 surge. That's how Gauteng Premier David Makhura has explained his cabinet reshuffle. Makhura has filled the vacant health MEC post following the axing of Bandile Masuku. Slindelo Masikane tells us who's in and who's out. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Preparing for the worst. Gauteng Premier David Makhura has announced a cabinet reshuffle in a bid to strengthen and support the department of health. Social development MEC Nomathemba Mokgethi moves to the Health Department with an intervention team in preparation for a possible COVID-19 infection surge. READ:Â Nomathemba Mokgethi appointed new Gauteng Health MEC Mokgethi is replaced by Morokane Mosupyoe, making way for Parks Tau as Economic development MEC. Makhura says the cabinet reshuffle is essential in ensuring that the province contains the spread of the virus while rebuilding the economy. * eNCA's Slindelo Masikane reports.